  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink234-kilavi">iṭaiviṭātu vantoḻukāniṉṟē kaḷavu nīṭāmal varaitaṟku muyalkiṉṟa talaimakaṉ talaimakaḷ vēṟupāṭu kaṇṭ itaṟkuk kāraṇam eṉṉeṉṟu viṉāviyavaḻi niṉṉaik kaṉaviṟ kaṇṭu viḻittukkāṇāḷāy vantateṉat tōḻi colli varaivu muṭukkiyatu.  </p>
      <p xml:lang="en"> What the confidante urged, saying,
        “It [her condition] came about because she saw you in a dream and, having woken, did not see you,”
        when the hero—who, having acted accordingly, coming without interval, 
        and who, seeing the change in the heroine and seeking to marry her,
        asked, “What is the reason for this?”
        
      </p>
    </div>

    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink234">
<l>miṉṉavir vayaṅkiḻai ñekiḻac cāay</l>
<l>naṉṉutal pacattal yāvatu tuṉṉik</l>
<l>kaṉaviṟ kāṇu mivaḷē</l>
<l>naṉaviṟ kāṇāṇiṉ mārpē teyyō</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Because her good forehead has become pale,</l>
        <l>having become exhausted so that her glowing jewels,</l>
        <l>shining like lightning, come loose,</l>
        <l>she indeed, who approaches anything and sees you in her dreams,</l>
        <l>does not see your chest in reality — alas!</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
